{%- comment -%} Privacy policy — for /pages/privacy {%- endcomment -%}
<section class="wa-page wa-page--legal wa-section--bleed" aria-labelledby="wa-privacy-title">
  <div class="wa-aurora" aria-hidden="true"><div class="wa-aurora__blob"></div></div>
  <div class="wa-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="wa-container wa-page__inner">
    <div class="wa-page__hero">
      <span class="wa-eyebrow">{{ 'wa.privacy.eyebrow' | t }}</span>
      <h1 id="wa-privacy-title" class="wa-page__title">
        {{ 'wa.privacy.title_a' | t }} <span class="wa-gradient-text">{{ 'wa.privacy.title_b' | t }}</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="wa-page__lede">
        {{ 'wa.privacy.lede' | t }}
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="wa-page__layout">
      <article class="wa-prose wa-page__article">

        <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Weird Artist is the trading name of an independent software studio
          shipping pay-once desktop applications. For data-protection
          questions, write to <a href="mailto:privacy@weirdartist.io">privacy@weirdartist.io</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What we collect &mdash; and why</h2>
        <h3>When you visit this site</h3>
        <p>
          Standard server logs (IP, user-agent, page, timestamp) kept for
          30 days for security and abuse prevention. We do not run third-party
          analytics or advertising trackers on this storefront.
        </p>

        <h3>When you buy a license</h3>
        <p>
          Shopify (our checkout processor) collects your name, email, billing
          address and payment details to process the order. We receive your
          name, email and order line items so we can deliver the download and
          handle support. See Shopify&rsquo;s own privacy notice for their
          processing terms.
        </p>

        <h3>When you use the desktop apps</h3>
        <p>
          The applications run locally. They do not send telemetry, usage
          analytics, keystrokes, file contents or crash reports to us by
          default. Update checks, when enabled, fetch a single version file
          and contain no identifying data beyond your IP at fetch time.
        </p>

        <h3>When you email us</h3>
        <p>
          We keep your message and reply in our mailbox so we can follow up.
          Standard inbox retention. Ask and we&rsquo;ll delete the thread.
        </p>

        <h2>3. What we never do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>No advertising trackers, no pixels, no third-party fingerprinting.</li>
          <li>No selling, renting or sharing of your data with brokers.</li>
          <li>No background telemetry from the desktop apps.</li>
          <li>No license servers that can disable your tool remotely.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This storefront uses only the cookies Shopify needs to run the cart
          and checkout (session, cart, locale, fraud prevention). No marketing
          or analytics cookies are loaded.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You can request a copy of, correction to, or deletion of any
          personal data we hold about you. Email
          <a href="mailto:privacy@weirdartist.io">privacy@weirdartist.io</a>
          and we&rsquo;ll respond within 30 days. EU/UK residents have the
          full set of GDPR rights including the right to lodge a complaint
          with your supervisory authority.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Server logs &mdash; 30 days.</li>
          <li>Order and license records &mdash; 7 years (tax law).</li>
          <li>Support emails &mdash; until the thread is resolved + 12 months, or until you ask us to delete it.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          If we change this policy materially, we&rsquo;ll bump the
          &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date below and post a note on the home
          page for at least 30 days. We won&rsquo;t change it retroactively
          to your detriment.
        </p>

        <p class="wa-page__meta">
          <span>Effective: 24 April 2026</span>
          <span>·</span>
          <span>Last updated: 24 April 2026</span>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
